{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C and grease a large loaf tin (900 g\/2 lb).","Place hazelnuts in bowl and chop <nobr>2 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>.","Add wholemeal flour, plain flour, bicarbonate of soda and salt then mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Add buttermilk, brown sugar and honey then stir <nobr>30 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Add pumpkin seeds, dates, raisins, cherries (if using) and orange zest then mix <nobr>20 sec\/\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Finish mixing by hand then transfer to prepared tin. Bake for 50 minutes-1 hour (180°C), covering with foil after 30 minutes if the top begins to brown too much, until a skewer inserted in centre comes out almost clean (see tip). Leave to cool in tin for 10 minutes then remove to a wire rack to cool completely.","Once cool, wrap loaf tightly in cling film then freeze for 30 minutes before slicing. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 150°C and line 2 large baking trays with baking paper.","Slice loaf thinly (2-3 mm) using a sharp knife and place slices on prepared baking trays. Bake for 10 minutes (150°C) then turn slices over and bake for a further 10 minutes (150°C) until golden. Transfer slices to a wire rack to cool and harden.","Serve or store in an airtight container for up to 5 days."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["butter, for greasing","90 g hazelnuts, blanched","120 g wholemeal flour","120 g plain flour","2 tsp bicarbonate of soda","½ tsp fine sea salt","450 g buttermilk","60 g dark brown sugar","75 g honey","65 g pumpkin seeds","75 g medjool dates, pitted, cut in thin strips","50 g raisins","45 g dried sour cherries              (optional)","1 orange, finely grated zest only"]}],"id":"r143872","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-qhYWvmWJ04o\/XZap8_8jflI\/AAAAAAAAhXI\/a52OvgPCKQgbrgMKDgMLQzji1JRa1GxLwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_I-wVLS1950YxnXDj.png","title":"Twice-Baked Fruit Toasts","publishedAt":"2017-04-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2.9 g","fat":"3.3 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"14.1 g","calories":"408 kJ \/ 98 kcal"},"usefulItems":"skewer, 900 g loaf tin (2 lb), aluminium foil, wire rack, 2 baking trays and baking paper, cling film, long sharp knife, airtight container, oven","hintsAndTricks":["When testing the baked loaf with a skewer, you may pierce a piece of fruit so it doesn't matter if not completely clean.","Bake in 2 smaller tins, for smaller slices.","Wrap resulting slices in cling film, for a softer, chewier result."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","6h 15m","30 slices"]}